docs.abstract: Jerome Powell, the chair of the Federal Reserve, was the latest central banker to express skepticism about Facebook’s cryptocurrency plans.

docs.lead_paragraph: Facebook is facing a growing chorus of doubts about its new Libra cryptocurrency project from authorities around the world, ahead of two congressional hearings on the initiative next week.

headline.main: Fed Chair Raises ‘Serious Concerns’ About Facebook’s Cryptocurrency Project
headline.print_headline: Facebook Navigating Growing Headwinds Over Cryptocurrency

docs.abstract: The retailer wants to draw more people into its stores, and it hopes that packing, labeling and shipping returns for the online behemoth will help.
docs.snippet: The retailer wants to draw more people into its stores, and it hopes that packing, labeling and shipping returns for the online behemoth will help.
docs.lead_paragraph: It says volumes about the challenges facing brick-and-mortar stores that the “single biggest initiative” out of Kohl’s this year, according to the national retailer’s chief executive, is that it will now accept and process unwanted orders from Amazon.

headline.main: Kohl’s Is Betting on Amazon Returns to Drive Sales
headline.print_headline: Kohl’s Joins With Amazon To Take Back Online Orders

docs.abstract: Companies like Microsoft see a multibillion-dollar opportunity to get more personal technology to workers who don’t sit behind a desk.
docs.snippet: Companies like Microsoft see a multibillion-dollar opportunity to get more personal technology to workers who don’t sit behind a desk.
docs.lead_paragraph: CHILLICOTHE, Ohio — When Toby Bouska Jr. started assembling cabs for Kenworth semitrucks last year, he learned the ropes by observing longtime workers at the factory. But it wasn’t exactly engaging, and he didn’t get much practice doing the job himself.

headline.main: You’re Hired. Now Wear This Headset to Learn the Job.
headline.print_headline: Tech Tools for the Factory Floor

docs.abstract: The statement is the latest indication that the Fed is likely to approve an interest-rate cut at its next meeting this month.

docs.abstract: Advertisers are increasingly turning to an invisible method that pulls together information about your device to pinpoint your identity.
docs.snippet: Advertisers are increasingly turning to an invisible method that pulls together information about your device to pinpoint your identity.
docs.lead_paragraph: If there’s one lesson to learn about digital privacy, it’s that we can never grow complacent. Even if we secure our data so we are not tracked online, the ad tech industry will find ways to monitor our digital activities.

headline.main: ‘Fingerprinting’ to Track Us Online Is on the Rise. Here’s What to Do.

docs.abstract: Sam Bell and his colleagues at Employ America want the central bank to cut interest rates now, and to lift them less quickly after the next recession, to create more jobs.
docs.snippet: Sam Bell and his colleagues at Employ America want the central bank to cut interest rates now, and to lift them less quickly after the next recession, to create more jobs.
docs.lead_paragraph: As President Trump rails against the Federal Reserve and urges it to lower interest rates, a similar push is coming from a group founded this year by three left-leaning millennials — albeit for very different reasons.

headline.main: Trump Isn’t Alone. These Millennials on the Left Want Low Interest Rates, Too.
headline.print_headline: Like Trump, These Leftists Want Low Interest Rates

docs.abstract: Last month, the social media company would not remove a doctored video of Speaker Nancy Pelosi. Facebook said the video of Mr. Zuckerberg will get the same treatment.
docs.snippet: Last month, the social media company would not remove a doctored video of Speaker Nancy Pelosi. Facebook said the video of Mr. Zuckerberg will get the same treatment.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Two weeks ago, Facebook declined to remove a doctored video in which the speaker of the House, Nancy Pelosi, seemed to drunkenly slur her speech. Over the weekend, two British artists released a doctored video of Facebook’s chief executive, Mark Zuckerberg, as a sly comment on the spread of false information online.

headline.main: A Fake Zuckerberg Video Challenges Facebook’s Rules
